2026-02-27 07:35:27 | IngestionPipeline | INFO | Extraction Completed: summary='Steven K. Galson is an American public health physician currently serving as Senior Vice President for Global Regulatory Affairs at Amgen and Professor-at-Large at the Keck Graduate Institute. He previously served as Acting Surgeon General of the United States and Assistant Secretary for Health.' domain='Professional' entities=[Entity(name='Steven K. Galson', type='Person', importance=0.5, isolated_context='Steven K. Galson (born 1956) is an American public health physician. He is currently Senior Vice President for Global Regulatory Affairs at Amgen, the S. California-based innovative global biopharmaceutical company. He is also Professor-at-Large at the Keck Graduate Institute for Applied Life Sciences in Clarmont, California. He is a retired rear admiral in the United States Public Health Service Commissioned Corps and public health administrator who served as the acting Surgeon General of the United States from October 1, 2007 – October 1, 2009. He served concurrently as acting Assistant Secretary for Health from January 22, 2009 to June 25, 2009, and as the Deputy Director and Director of the Center for Drug Evaluation and Research (CDER) at the Food and Drug Administration from 2001 to 2007. As the Acting Surgeon General, he was the commander of the United States Public Health Service Commissioned Corps and, while serving as the Assistant Secretary for Health, was the operational head of the Public Health Service.'), Entity(name='Amgen', type='Organization', importance=0.5, isolated_context='Steven K. Galson (born 1956) is an American public health physician. He is currently Senior Vice President for Global Regulatory Affairs at Amgen, the S. California-based innovative global biopharmaceutical company. He is also Professor-at-Large at the Keck Graduate Institute for Applied Life Sciences in Clarmont, California.'), Entity(name='Keck Graduate Institute', type='Organization', import